  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Peel and thinly slice the red onion, then place it in a small bowl and separate the rings.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together cumin, smoked paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Coat the ramekin with a thin layer of olive oil.",
    "Add the sliced red onion to the ramekin, followed by the spice mixture, garlic, parsley, and cilantro.",
    "Drizzle the vegetable broth, honey, and lemon juice over the onion mixture.",
    "Cover the ramekin with aluminum foil and bake for 30 minutes.",
    "Remove the foil and continue baking for an additional 15-20 minutes, or until the onion is caramelized and tender.",
    "Let the tagine rest for 5 minutes before serving."
  ],
